# Development Plan

## Introduction

This document outlines the phase-wise development plan for the Society360 â€“ Smart Residential Management System. The plan follows a structured Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC) approach and aligns with the CivoraX Internship Program task flow.

---

## Development Methodology

The project follows a **phased and incremental development approach**, allowing core features to be implemented, tested, and refined progressively.

---

## Phase 1: System Design & Planning

### Objectives
- Finalize system architecture
- Design database schema
- Define security implementation plan
- Set up project repositories and environment

### Deliverables
- Architecture documentation
- Database design documentation
- Security design documentation
- Initial project setup

---

## Phase 2: Authentication & User Management

### Objectives
- Implement secure user authentication
- Enforce role-based access control
- Create user and role management APIs

### Deliverables
- Login and registration functionality
- JWT-based authentication
- Role-restricted dashboards

---

## Phase 3: Visitor & Maintenance Modules

### Objectives
- Develop visitor pre-approval and logging features
- Implement maintenance request workflows
- Enable real-time status tracking

### Deliverables
- Visitor management module
- Maintenance & complaint module
- Status update mechanisms

---

## Phase 4: Finance & Communication Modules

### Objectives
- Implement billing and payment simulation
- Develop announcements and notification features
- Integrate reporting dashboards

### Deliverables
- Billing and payment module
- Communication & announcement module
- Administrative reports

---

## Phase 5: Testing & Refinement

### Objectives
- Perform functional and security testing
- Fix bugs and optimize performance
- Improve UI/UX consistency

### Deliverables
- Tested and stable application
- Test reports
- Optimized user experience

---

## Phase 6: Documentation & Final Submission

### Objectives
- Finalize all documentation
- Prepare final project report
- Push final code to GitHub

### Deliverables
- Complete documentation set
- Final source code repository
- Internship project submission

---

## Tools & Workflow

- Version Control: Git & GitHub
- Issue Tracking: GitHub Issues
- Continuous Integration (Optional): GitHub Actions

---

## Conclusion

This development plan ensures structured progress, quality assurance, and timely completion of the Society360 project while meeting academic and industry standards.
